  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place the chicken thighs skin-side down on a chopping board. Run a knife along each side of the bone to expose the bone. Using scissors, cut underneath the bone to remove it. Repeat with the remaining chicken thighs."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the courgette in half lengthways and then into half moons. Cut the red onion into large chunks."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Season the chicken with salt and pepper and add skin side down into a cold, large frying pan and set it over a medium heat. Cook for 10-15 mins until the chicken skin is golden brown."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the chicken is cooking, make the tzatziki. Grate the cucumber into a bowl and season with salt. Set aside for 5 mins then squeeze out the excess water. Meanwhile, chop the dill then add to the squeezed cucumber along with the yoghurt, the zest of the lemon and the juice of ½ the lemon. Grate in the garlic. Mix well to combine then season to taste with salt. Set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the chicken skin is golden brown and crispy, flip the chicken thighs and cook for a further 2 mins. Remove them from the pan and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the red onion, courgette and spices to the pan. Grate in the garlic then cook over a medium heat until soft. (If anything catches on the bottom of the pan, just add a little water and scrape it up). Add the drained chickpeas and cooked rice to the pan. Cook over a medium heat for 2-3 mins until everything has come together. Season with salt, pepper and MSG."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, pick the parsley leaves and cut the chicken into thick slices."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, divide the rice between Tupperware containers then top with the chicken and tzatziki. Sprinkle over the parsley and finish with a lemon wedge. Pop in the fridge until needed."
    }
  ],
